overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  which included a detailed specification for its functionality, diagnostic
  capabilities, and reporting. The agent systematically identified several gaps
  and missing features, such as a tiredness severity scale with safety
  messaging, detection for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, weighted
  scoring for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness, and the inclusion of outbound links
  in reports. The agent then proceeded to implement all these identified items.
  This involved updating data types, validation schemas, UI components for
  input, and complex logic within the report generation for both web and PDF
  formats. Additionally, the CSV export was significantly enhanced to include
  all flattened questionnaire responses, and new sections for pain/chronic
  fatigue screening and medical/mental health history were added. The
  implementation ensures the application now meets the comprehensive
  requirements outlined in the initial specification.
